The paper discusses a logical framework for defining and checking process equivalences, which falls under the category of formal methods. The use of modal fixpoint logic suggests a focus on logic and semantics, which is consistent with the sub-category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The paper also discusses model checking and symbolic evaluation, which are techniques commonly used in Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Software Engineering (cs.SE). The paper's focus on process equivalences and the linear-time branching-time spectrum suggests a connection to Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL) and Linear-Time Temporal Logic (cs.LT).
